==============================================================================================================
  POSITIONAL VALUE PREMIUM ANALYSIS
==============================================================================================================

  The positional adjustment built into BRAVS (per 162 games):
       C: +12.5 runs
      SS: +7.5 runs
      CF: +2.5 runs
      2B: +2.5 runs
      3B: +2.5 runs
      LF: -7.5 runs
      RF: -7.5 runs
      1B: -12.5 runs
      DH: -17.5 runs

  This means a catcher with identical offensive stats to a DH gets
  +30 runs of positional credit per full season — roughly 3 extra wins.
  Johnny Bench and Buster Posey benefit enormously from this premium.

  Relievers produce low raw BRAVS due to limited innings, but their
  high-leverage contexts generate leverage multiplier boosts that
  partially compensate.


